*facepalm*  Evidently you didn't understand my meaning.

Every part has a drag arrow.  Every part has a drag arrow.  The fairing sections of ProcFairings are parts, as are the bases, so they get drag arrows.  The fairing sections of stock fairings are not parts, and so don't get drag arrows; their drag effects are merged into the drag arrow for their base.

Number of arrows has jack to do with the actual forces applied.  Total length of all arrows has to do with force applied.  So since you don't see the big arrow centered at the fairing origin on stock and KW fairings, you assume, "oh, it makes less drag despite having the same shape" despite that not being true at all.

So, yeah, the number of arrows visible correlates to the number of nodes because, surprise surprise, the number of nodes controls the number of fairing parts.
